<table width="auto"  border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0"><tr><td colspan=3>House Bill/Resolution NO. <b>HR00928</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>FULL TITLE : RESOLUTION URGING THE COMMITTEE ON ENERGY TO CONDUCT AN INQUIRY, IN AID OF LEGISLATION, ON THE OVERALL SITUATION OF THE POWER PLANTS LOCATED IN THE LUZON GRID, CONSIDERING THE SPATE AND OVERLAPPING EXTENT OF POWER PLANT SHUTDOWNS, INCLUDING THE MASSIVE MAINTENANCE SHUTDOWNS OF AT LEAST TWENTY (20) POWER PLANTS DURING SUMMERTIME AND OTHER CONSEQUENT SHUTDOWNS THAT WOULD DEFINITELY COST IMMENSE ELECTRICITY RATE HIKES TO THE DETRIMENT OF OUR CONSUMERS, WITH THE END IN VIEW THAT PRO-PEOPLE MEASURES AND REFORMS BE INSTITUTED TO PROTECT THE CONSUMERS FROM THESE SEEMINGLY COLLUSIVE AND MANIPULATIVE PRACTICES</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PRINCIPAL AUTHOR/S : <b>ZARATE, CARLOS ISAGANI T.</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>DATE FILED : 2017-04-19</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>COMMITEE HEARINGS/ACTIONS:</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3><b>&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp&nbsp1. Referred to Stakeholders on 2017-05-24</b><tr><td colspan=3><b>ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE COMMITTEE ON RULES</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>REFERRAL TO THE COMMITTEE ON ENERGY ON 2017-05-09</td></tr><tr><td colspan=3>PREVIOUS COMMITTEE REFERRALS :PRIMARILY REFERRED TO RULES on 2017-05-03;</td></tr></table>